abstract: Cobbling a coalition out of “Lower Alabama,” a Midwest-like midsection, a tropical megalopolis and more can be tricky.
snippet: Cobbling a coalition out of “Lower Alabama,” a Midwest-like midsection, a tropical megalopolis and more can be tricky.
lead_paragraph: TALLAHASSEE, Fla. — After enduring two decades of Republican statewide rule, Florida Democrats are pursuing a novel strategy to reclaim the Governor’s Mansion — one that would have been unthinkable even a few years ago. They are rallying behind a young, unapologetically liberal African-American candidate in a swing state where older conservative white voters have dominated five straight midterms.

abstract: With Republicans confident about holding onto their Senate majority, the party is fortifying defenses in conservative-leaning districts that were considered secure but now may be at risk.
snippet: With Republicans confident about holding onto their Senate majority, the party is fortifying defenses in conservative-leaning districts that were considered secure but now may be at risk.
lead_paragraph: CINCINNATI — As the 2018 midterm campaign enters its final full week, House Republicans are rushing to fortify their defenses in conservative-leaning districts they thought were secure, pouring millions of dollars into a last-minute bid to build a new firewall against Democrats.

abstract: Washington State voters will consider carbon fees aimed at curbing climate change. If they approve, the state will be the first in the nation to impose the fees.
snippet: Washington State voters will consider carbon fees aimed at curbing climate change. If they approve, the state will be the first in the nation to impose the fees.
lead_paragraph: CENTRALIA, Wash. — The last coal mine in Washington State closed down about a decade ago in Centralia, about 65 miles south of Seattle, leaving scars on the land and the local economy. Now, a solar electricity project — perhaps the largest in the state — is planned for the same location, by the same company that once ran the mine.

abstract: Mayor Bill de Blasio is poised to end a program that sent children to poorly performing schools even as officials knew they had little hope of improving.
snippet: Mayor Bill de Blasio is poised to end a program that sent children to poorly performing schools even as officials knew they had little hope of improving.
lead_paragraph: Mayor Bill de Blasio promised to “shake the foundations of New York City education” in 2014 with a new program called Renewal, a signature effort to improve the city’s 94 poorest-performing schools by showering them with millions of dollars in social services and teacher training.

abstract: National Democratic Party committees and super PACs outraised their Republican counterparts this month, but the Republican committees had more money in the bank as of last week.
snippet: National Democratic Party committees and super PACs outraised their Republican counterparts this month, but the Republican committees had more money in the bank as of last week.
lead_paragraph: The 2018 midterm elections are expected to shatter spending records, and campaign finance reports filed on Thursday provided a glimpse inside frenzied final fund-raising pushes, while revealing how much money each side has left to spend in the final weeks before Election Day.

abstract: New ads from Senate Democrats show vulnerable incumbents moving away from left-wing elements. On the Republican front, want to know how the party is feeling about the Senate? Watch Air Force One.

abstract: While Google, Facebook and Twitter face scrutiny for spreading misinformation, Apple has avoided scandal by using people to pick what news to show. Is that good for news outlets?
snippet: While Google, Facebook and Twitter face scrutiny for spreading misinformation, Apple has avoided scandal by using people to pick what news to show. Is that good for news outlets?
lead_paragraph: Many of Apple’s employees moved into a glistening new $5 billion glass headquarters in Cupertino, Calif., this year. A mile west, at Apple’s old campus on 1 Infinite Loop, a project antithetical to Silicon Valley’s ethos is now underway.

abstract: Representative Carlos Curbelo is a perennial target for Democrats. His political fate might be an indicator of national trends in the 2018 midterms.
snippet: Representative Carlos Curbelo is a perennial target for Democrats. His political fate might be an indicator of national trends in the 2018 midterms.
lead_paragraph: MARATHON, Fla. — If Representative Carlos Curbelo clings to his seat in Congress come November, defying the political odds for a moderate Republican in one of the nation’s most competitive districts, it will be in part because of people like Gary Graves, the owner of a Florida Keys seafood business. His spiny lobster catch has been hit with costly tariffs as part of the White House’s trade war with China, yet he supports President Trump, and Mr. Curbelo, anyway.
